abstract: Notwithstanding the inclement state of the weather, a large number of citizens of Jersey City and Hoboken assembled in the Catholic Institute, on Third street, Jersey City, last evening, to ratify the nomination of Hon. abstract: While it must be admitted that the Democratic Convention, which concluded its labors yesterday, was eminently respectable in appearance, it is equally true that it was wholly without heart in its work. So utterly devoid was it of life that the position of Chairman was a sinecure, and it was, at the same time, the most orderly and quiet of all possible conventions.
